<refentry xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="function.imagickdraw-getstrokemiterlimit">
 <refnamediv>
  <refname>ImagickDraw::getStrokeMiterLimit</refname>
  <refpurpose>Returns the stroke miter limit</refpurpose>
 </refnamediv>

 <refsect1 role="description">
  &reftitle.description;
  <methodsynopsis>
   <type>int</type><methodname>ImagickDraw::getStrokeMiterLimit</methodname>
   <void/>
  </methodsynopsis>
  &warn.undocumented.func;
  &warn.experimental.func;
  <para>
   Returns the miter limit. When two line segments meet at a sharp angle and miter joins have been specified for 'lineJoin', it is possible for the miter to extend far beyond the thickness of the line stroking the path. The miterLimit' imposes a limit on the ratio of the miter length to the 'lineWidth'.
  </para>
 </refsect1>

 <refsect1 role="parameters">
  &reftitle.parameters;
  <para>
  </para>

 </refsect1>
 <refsect1 role="returnvalues">
  &reftitle.returnvalues;
  <para>
   Returns an int describing the miter limit
   and 0 if no miter limit is set.
  </para>
 </refsect1>

